## Why Firestore for Offline-First?

### Firestore Strengths

✅ **Built-in offline support** - Local cache handles reads/writes  
✅ **Automatic sync** - Queues writes, syncs when online  
✅ **Real-time updates** - Other devices get changes automatically  
✅ **Managed infrastructure** - No server to maintain  
✅ **Scalable** - Handles growth without re-architecture

### When to Use Firestore vs SQLite

| Use Case | Recommendation |
|----------|----------------|
| **Multi-device sync** | Firestore |
| **Offline-only, no sync** | SQLite |
| **Complex relational queries** | SQLite (or Firestore + denormalization) |
| **Real-time collaboration** | Firestore |
| **Cost-sensitive at scale** | SQLite + custom sync (more work) |

